.TH OKUCC 1 "16 June 2026" "OKU Foundation" "Usage Manual"
.SH NAME
.B okucc
\(en the minimalist Oku C compiler
.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBokucc\fP
.RB [ -cES ]
.RB [ -o
.IR outfile ]
.RB [ -I
.IR include_dir ]
.RB [ --freestanding ]
.RB [ --pure-syscalls ]
.RI [ file \0...]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The
.B okucc
utility is a minimalist, high-performance C compiler designed for the OKU
ecosystem. It translates C source files into optimized native machine code.
In alignment with the OKU philosophy,
.B okucc
prioritizes predictable code generation, minimal compilation overhead, and 
eschews unnecessary runtime bloat. It is designed to interface seamlessly with 
low-level software architectures and bare-metal environments.

By default,
.B okucc
targets the native host architecture (such as x86-64) and generates code 
optimized for direct hardware execution.

.SH OPTIONS

.IP \fB-c\fP
Compile or assemble the source files, but do not link. The linking stage is 
skipped, and the compiler outputs raw object files.
.IP \fB-E\fP
Stop after the preprocessing stage. Do not run the compiler proper. The 
output is preprocessed source code sent to standard output.
.IP \fB-I\fP\ \fIinclude_dir\fP
Add the directory
.I include_dir
to the list of directories to be searched for header files during 
preprocessing. This option can be specified multiple times to add multiple 
directories.
.IP \fB-o\fP\ \fIoutfile\fP
Place the primary output in
.IR outfile .
If this option is not specified, the default executable name is \(oqa.out\(cq.
.IP \fB-S\fP
Stop after the compilation stage proper; do not assemble. The output is a 
human-readable text file containing target assembly code.
.IP \fB--freestanding\fP
Directs the compiler to target a freestanding environment. In this mode, 
the compiler makes no assumptions about the presence of a standard C library 
runtime layer, ensuring that the generated code is completely self-contained.
.IP \fB--pure-syscalls\fP
Forces the compiler to inline direct kernel system calls rather than emitting 
external calls to a standard library runtime (such as libc). This mirrors 
the design paradigms of the TAQBOL programming language ecosystem.

.SH INPUT FILES

The utility accepts source files ending with the following extensions:
.IP \fB.c\fP
C source files to be preprocessed, compiled, and optionally linked.
.IP \fB.i\fP
Preprocessed C source files ready for direct compilation.
.IP \fB.s\fP
Assembly language files to be sent directly to the assembler stage.

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.IP \fBOKU_INCLUDE_PATH\fP
A colon-separated list of directories searched for header files, processed 
after directories specified via the
.B -I
command-line option.

.SH STANDARDS

The
.B okucc
compiler implements a strict, predictable subset of modern ISO C standards, 
optimizing for readability of output and performance of implementation over 
convolved implementation edge-cases.

By default, all compilation pipelines produce optimized freestanding code. 
Integration with external linkers and standard runtimes is conditionally 
supported but discouraged under baseline configurations.

